@host = http://localhost:5083
@apikey = dev-api-key-1

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# CREATE_USER
# Description: Create a new user "Evan".
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 201 Created
#  - Content-Type: application/json
#  - Body: created user object with numeric "id", e.g.
#    { "id": 5, "userName":"Evan", "userAge":35, "role":"Guest" }
# Notes:
#  - We capture the response to use the created id in later requests.
### CREATE_USER
POST {{host}}/users
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "Evan",
  "userAge": 35,
  "role": "Guest"
}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# GET_CREATED_USER
# Description: Retrieve the user created by CREATE_USER using captured id.
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 200 OK
#  - Content-Type: application/json
#  - Body: the user object matching the created id
# Notes:
#  - Uses captured id from CREATE_USER.response.body.$.id
### GET_CREATED_USER
GET {{host}}/users/{{CREATE_USER.response.body.$.id}}
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# UPDATE_CREATED_USER
# Description: Update the user created earlier.
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 200 OK
#  - Content-Type: application/json
#  - Body: updated user object with same id and new fields
### UPDATE_CREATED_USER
PUT {{host}}/users/{{CREATE_USER.response.body.$.id}}
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "Evan Updated",
  "userAge": 36,
  "role": "Guest"
}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# DELETE_CREATED_USER
# Description: Delete the user created earlier.
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 200 OK
#  - Content-Type: application/json
#  - Body: { "message": "User with id X deleted" }
### DELETE_CREATED_USER
DELETE {{host}}/users/{{CREATE_USER.response.body.$.id}}
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# LIST_USERS
# Description: List users with pagination.
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 200 OK
#  - Content-Type: application/json
#  - Body: { page, pageSize, total, items: [...] }
### LIST_USERS
GET {{host}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# CREATE_USER_BAD_AGE
# Description: Create user with wrong type for userAge (string).
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 400 Bad Request
#  - Content-Type: application/problem+json
#  - Body: ProblemDetails or ValidationProblemDetails describing the error
# Notes:
#  - Our global middleware should return application/problem+json with details.
### CREATE_USER_BAD_AGE
POST {{host}}/users
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "AgeAsString",
  "userAge": "thirty",
  "role": "User"
}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# GET_NONINT_ID
# Description: Request with non-integer id (route mismatch).
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 404 Not Found
#  - Content-Type: application/problem+json
#  - Body: ProblemDetails with type "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.5.1"
# Notes:
#  - Previously returned plain text; normalized middleware should return ProblemDetails.
### GET_NONINT_ID
GET {{host}}/users/abc
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# GET_NOT_FOUND
# Description: Request a user id that does not exist.
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 404 Not Found
#  - Content-Type: application/problem+json
#  - Body: ProblemDetails with type "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.5.1"
# Notes:
#  - If endpoint returns custom JSON { "error": "..."} middleware will normalize it.
### GET_NOT_FOUND
GET {{host}}/users/999999
X-Api-Key: {{apikey}}

###

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# UNAUTHENTICATED_REQUEST
# Description: Attempt to access a protected endpoint without X-Api-Key header.
# Expectation:
#  - Status: 401 Unauthorized
#  - Content-Type: application/problem+json
#  - Body: ProblemDetails with type "https://example.com/probs/unauthorized" and status 401
# Notes:
#  - This request intentionally omits the X-Api-Key header to verify the auth middleware.
### UNAUTHENTICATED_REQUEST
GET {{host}}/users
# no X-Api-Key header on purpose

###

